hal (0.5.10~git20070925-1osso1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New downstream git snapshot.
    - Stop reading from the USB cable sysfs file, which just got removed.
      Map the values for cable_type from the mode sysfs file for now, until
      it gets completely deprecated. (Fixes: NB#70370)
    - Remove code to workaround the flaky kernel USB mode notifications,
      which now should be working fine.

 -- Guillem Jover <guillem.jover@nokia.com>  Tue, 25 Sep 2007 19:35:13 +0300

hal (0.5.10~git20070917-1osso1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New downstream git snapshot.
    - Use hardcoded sysfs path for the ACPI code which was causing a build
      failure on i386 due to a call to the no longer existing function to
      generate the path at runtime (this patch seems to have been lost
      somewhen somehow).
    - Use changesets in addon-mmc and probe-net-bluetooth.

